{"lemma":"قَرِيبٍ","slug":"قَرِيبٍ","root":"ق.ر.ب","root_slug":"ق-ر-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ق-ر-ب","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"قَرِيب","root":"قرب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":26},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n35405"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%82%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%A8%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"near, close, adjacent","examples":[{"text":"[…] إِنَّ رَحْمَةَ ٱللّٰهِ قَرِيبٌ مِنَ ٱلْمُحْسِنِينَ","english":"[…] Indeed, the mercy of Allah is near to the doers of good."},{"text":"[…] لَعَلَّ ٱلسَّاعَةَ قَرِيبٌ","english":"[…] Perhaps the Hour is near."}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"simple, easily understood"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"relative; relation"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"فَعِيل (faʕīl)-type stative-verb derived from the active participle from the verb قَرُبَ (qaruba, “to be near”). Cognate with Hebrew קָרוֹב (karóv, “close, near”) and Amharic ቅርብ (k’ɨrb)."},"ipa":["/qa.riːb/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n35405","headword_ar":"قَرِيبٌ","root":"qrb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Near in respect of place:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K, * &c.:) in this sense used alike as sing. and pl. (Kh, ISk, T, O, Msb, K *) and dual, (ISk, TA,) and as masc. and fem., (AA, Kh, Fr, ISk, T, S, O, Msb,) as is also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEiydN","text_ar":"بَعِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the contr. sense: (Kh, ISk, TA:) the Arabs say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa qariybN","text_ar":"هُوَ قَرِيبٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"min~iY","text_ar":"مِنِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (ISk, O, * TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humaA qariybN min~iY","text_ar":"هُمَا قَرِيبٌ مِنِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo","text_ar":"هُمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qariybN min~iY","text_ar":"قَرِيبٌ مِنِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (ISk, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hiYa qariybN min~iY","text_ar":"هِىَ قَرِيبٌ مِنِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c., meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY makaAnK qariybK","text_ar":"فِى مَكَانٍ قَرِيبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a place near,"},{"kind":"text","text":"to me, or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"little removed"},{"kind":"text","text":"from me:] (ISk, O, TA:) or when you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hinodN qariybN minoka","text_ar":"هِنْدٌ قَرِيبٌ مِنْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", it is as though you said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hinodN mawoDiEuhaA qariybN minoka","text_ar":"هِنْدٌ مَوْضِعُهَا قَرِيبٌ مِنْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hind, her place is near to thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (AA, Msb:) hence, [in the Kur vii. 54,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a raHomapa A@ll~`hi qariybN mina AlmuHosiniyna","text_ar":"اـِنَّ رَحْمَةَ ا@للّٰهِ قَرِيبٌ مِنَ المُحْسِنِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily the mercy of God is near unto the welldoers"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (AA, ISk, O, Msb:) but it is allowable to say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qariybapN","text_ar":"قَرِيبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEiydapN","text_ar":"بَعِيدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (ISk, O, Msb, TA:) or (accord. to Zj, TA)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qryb","text_ar":"قريب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is here without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rHmp","text_ar":"رحمة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not really [but only conventionally] of the fem. gender: (S, O, TA:) [but this reason is not satisfactory, because it does not apply to other cases mentioned above:] and it is also said that it is without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"because it is assimilated to an epithet of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEuwlN","text_ar":"فَعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which does not receive the fem. affix"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [Hence the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino qariybK","text_ar":"مِنْ قَرِيبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qurobN","text_ar":"قُرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", former half, in two places. And [hence also] you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a qariybFA","text_ar":"اـِنَّ قَرِيبًا"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2508},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"minoka zayodFA","text_ar":"مِنْكَ زَيْدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily Zeyd is in a place near to thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; like as you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a qurobaka zayodFA","text_ar":"اـِنَّ قُرْبَكَ زَيْدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Sb, TA.) ―         -b2-  [Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Near in respect of time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"whether future, as in the Kur xlii. 16, &c.; or past, as in the Kur lix. 15. And hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qariybFA","text_ar":"قَرِيبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Shortly"},{"kind":"text","text":"after and before. And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Nearly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as when one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqamotu biAlmawoDiEi qariybFA mino sanapK","text_ar":"اَقَمْتُ بِالمَوْضِعِ قَرِيبًا مِنْ سَنَةٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I remained, stayed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abode, in the place nearly a year."},{"kind":"text","text":"Hence also the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano qariybK","text_ar":"عَنْ قَرِيبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qurobN","text_ar":"قُرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", near the middle. ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Near"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"related by birth"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by marriage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K:) [and generally used as an epithet in which the quality of a subst. is predominant, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a relation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relative:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] in this sense it receives the fem. form, by universal consent; so that you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*ihi AlmaroA^apu qariybatiY","text_ar":"هٰذِهِ المَرْاَةُ قَرِيبَتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This woman is my relation"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Fr, S, O, Msb: *) and likewise the dual form; so that you say, ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humaA qariybaAni","text_ar":"هُمَا قَرِيبَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humaA qariybataAni","text_ar":"هُمَا قَرِيبَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They two are relations"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (AA, Msb:) [and it has a pl., namely,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqoribaA='u","text_ar":"اَقْرِبَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo A^aqoribaAy^iY","text_ar":"هُمْ اَقْرِبَايِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqaAribiY","text_ar":"اَقَارِبِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O, K) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqorabiY~a","text_ar":"اَقْرَبِىَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", this last originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqorabuwYa","text_ar":"اَقْرَبُوىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the first signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are my relations;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the second and third, properly, being pls. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqorabu","text_ar":"اَقْرَبُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are my nearer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nearest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very near, relations;"},{"kind":"text","text":"though in the T the second is said to be pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qariybN","text_ar":"قَرِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and in most of the copies of the K, but not in all, (for in some the first of these three words is omitted, as it is also in the TA,) it is implied that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqoribaA='u","text_ar":"اَقْرِبَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqaAribu","text_ar":"اَقَارِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqorabuwna","text_ar":"اَقْرَبُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(which are mentioned in the Msb without any distinction of meaning) are all to be understood in the latter sense]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qurobN","text_ar":"قُرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[also] is a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qariybN","text_ar":"قَرِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. in the sense here assigned to it], like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gurobN","text_ar":"غُرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gariybN","text_ar":"غَرِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zlf","text_ar":"زلف"},{"kind":"text","text":";) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qarobaY","text_ar":"قَرْبَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is allowable as a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariybN","text_ar":"فَرِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T, TA:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qariybapN","text_ar":"قَرِيبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraAy^ibu","text_ar":"قَرَايِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, Msb, TA.) And like as you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa qariybiY","text_ar":"هُوَ قَرِيبِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is my relation"},{"kind":"text","text":"], as too you say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa *uw qaraAbatiY","text_ar":"هُوَ ذُو قَرَابَتِى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"min~iY","text_ar":"مِنِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw qaraAbapK","text_ar":"ذُو قَرَابَةٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn~Y","text_ar":"منّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw maqorubapK","text_ar":"ذُو مَقْرُبَةٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"min~iY","text_ar":"مِنِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw qurobaY","text_ar":"ذُو قُرْبَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) but not ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa qaraAbatiY","text_ar":"هُوَ قَرَابَتِى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) [for only] the vulgar say this; as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo qaraAbaAtiY","text_ar":"هُمْ قَرَابَاتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O:) or, accord. to Z, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa qaraAbatiY","text_ar":"هُوَ قَرَابَتِى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is allowable, being accounted for as a phrase in which the prefixed n. ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw","text_ar":"ذُو"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is suppressed; and it has moreover been asserted to be correct and chaste in verse and prose: ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraAbapN","text_ar":"قَرَابَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also occurs in the trads. in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqaAribu","text_ar":"اَقَارِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": it is said in the Nh to be an inf. n. used as an epithet, agreeably with general analogy: and in the Tes-heel it is said to be a quasi-pl. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qariybN","text_ar":"قَرِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHaAbapN","text_ar":"صَحَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAHibN","text_ar":"صَاحِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (MF, TA:) [accord. to Mtr,] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraAbapN","text_ar":"قَرَابَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is correctly applicable to one and to a pl. number, as being originally an inf. n.; so that one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huw qaraAbatiY","text_ar":"هُو قَرَابَتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo qaraAbatiY","text_ar":"هُمْ قَرَابَتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; though the chaste phrase is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw","text_ar":"ذُو"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraAbatiY","text_ar":"قَرَابَتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to one; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*awaA qaraAbatiY","text_ar":"ذَوَا قَرَابَتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", to two; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*awuw qaraAbatiY","text_ar":"ذَوُو قَرَابَتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", to a pl. number. (Mgh.) ―         -b4-  And [it is also applied to relationship:] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayonanaA nasabN qariybN","text_ar":"بَيْنَنَا نَسَبٌ قَرِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quraAbN","text_ar":"قُرَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Between us is a near relationship"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b5-  It signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Near,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"allied, by affection and friendship."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tanas~aba","text_ar":"تَنَسَّبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN qariybN mina Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ قَرِيبٌ مِنَ النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is near,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"friendly and affectionate, to people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mankind."},{"kind":"text","text":"] See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qurobaAnN","text_ar":"قُرْبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last sentence. ―         -b6-  And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA huwa biEaAlimK","text_ar":"مَا هُوَ بِعَالِمٍ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAlimK","text_ar":"عَالِمٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA quraAbi","text_ar":"وَلَا قُرَابِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAlimK","text_ar":"عَالِمٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quraAbapi","text_ar":"قُرَابَةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qariybi EaAlimK","text_ar":"قَرِيبِ عَالِمٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is not learned nor near learned"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino *`lika","text_ar":"مِنْ ذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA huwa bi$abiyhika walaA biquraAbapK","text_ar":"مَا هُوَ بِشَبِيهِكَ وَلَا بِقُرَابَةٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA biqariybK mino *`lika","text_ar":"وَلَا بِقَرِيبٍ مِنْ ذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is not the like of thee nor near that"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, O;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"minoka","text_ar":"مِنْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA biquraAbapK","text_ar":"وَلَا بِقُرَابَةٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bqariybK","text_ar":"بقَرِيبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor near"},{"kind":"text","text":"the like of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN qariybu Alv~araY","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ قَرِيبُ الثَّرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qariybu Alv~araY baEiydu","text_ar":"قَرِيبُ الثَّرَى بَعِيدُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~abaTi","text_ar":"النَّبَطِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see in arts."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vrY","text_ar":"ثرى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nbT","text_ar":"نبط"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also, (O, K, TA,) but in some of the lexicons written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qir~iybN","text_ar":"قِرِّيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Salted fish, while yet in its recent, moist, state."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["ISk","TA","AA","Kh","Fr","T","S","O","Msb","K","A","MF"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}